Here are a handfull of Ideas ive come up with over the months...
 
Craft Trap - Level 70
The art of setting traps is one of the greatest weapons
of any Ranger. It also goes hand in hand with the art
of creating the traps. More than aquestion of supplies, 
this skill is focused mainly on theingenious of the Ranger
crafting a trap. The more intelligent, the more effective 
the traps the Ranger mightbe able to come up with.
Craft Trap will allow a Ranger to create a trap, given
he is in a wooded area, for most of the supplies needed
can be found there. The higher the skill percentage, the
more likely the Ranger is to succeed in creating the trap
of choice. There are two types of traps he can create, one
being like an ordinary trap that a Ranger can buy at a
hunting or Ranger supply store that can be stored and set
upon need. The second kind is a trap that cannot be built
into a kit, and must be prepared and set on the spot. Though
this may be harder to use, these traps are hugely more effective.
Once a Ranger has practiced this skill, he can use it. When used,
by typing in "craft" or "crafttrap" a list will be displayed of
settable traps. The higher the intelligence of the Ranger, the
more traps that will be displayed under this list. Some traps
available:
Intelligence 10 - Trip Trap
-This is merely a rope stretched across a path, tripping anyone
to pass-
(This is a kit trap that when set will trip the victim and 
 lose them 50 movement points)
Itelligence 15 - Pit Fall
-Obviously, a covered pit that will cause the first person walking
by to fall in)
(This is a on-the-spot set trap that causes the victim to 
 be stunned for 1 tic and lose 75 movement points)
Intelligence 20 - Log Trap
-A log tied back, suspended from vines or rope. When tripped,
 the log is released, striking the victim-
 
(This would be a kit trap that when set will deal damage
 and cause the victim to fall to the ground losing 75 
 movement points)
Intelligence 25 - Spiked Pit Fall
-Just like the pit fall, except with spikes, ouch!-
(This is a on-the-spot set trap that causes the victim
 to be stunned for 1 tic, take moderate damage, and lose
 100 movement points)
Intelligence 30 - Fly Trap
-The Fly trap is a web of vines with heavy stones weaved into its  design. When tripped, the net swings down from above quickly and   strikes the victim from the front, causing them to become entangled-
(This is a kit trap that causes 300 movement points and trips the  victim)
Intelligence 35 - Hunters Net
-This is a trap designed to catch large and dangerous prey. It is a net
 that is hidden amongst the leaves and foliage on the ground, and when  victim is in the middle of it, the trap is tripped, raising the victim  up into  the trees, trapped-
(This is an on-the-spot trap that causes the victim to be "entangled"
 for 5 tics)
A new skill could be granted to all classes (or maybe just the stronger 
classes) called "Struggle". This skill will attempt to free the user when "entangled". This skills effectiveness is based on skill percentage and strength. Three successful attempts must be made before the "entangled" effect will be negated. This skill could begin at 50% for all fighter classes, and if given to mages, starting at 0%.
-----------------------------------------------------------------------
Woodland Healer - Level 50
As a survivalist, Rangers have gone further than any, except maybe the druid, in using the world around him or her to live and be healthy. It is second nature to a Ranger the right mixtures of plants to produce a salve or balm with healing properties. 
This skill is usable only in a wooded area. It can be used on himself or an ally. It will heal a small ammount, 50-100 hp, and cure poison and plague. The skill should take several seconds to work. 
Syntax: cure (or) heal <target>
<User name> begins mixing a healing balm from nearby plants.
(a few seconds)
<User name> applies a healing balm to <target>.
Alternative:
The Woodland Healer skill could have a different effect depending on where the Ranger is, in a swamp, forest, hills, ect. So depending on the avaialable plants, the Ranger can mix a different sort of salve or balm. It would be up to Ranger to learn what sort of effects the balm or salve will have depending on the terrain.
-----------------------------------------------------------------------
Pivot Block - Level 75
The spear is an ideal hunting weapon, one Rangers have excelled in using. A particularly skilled Ranger has learnt to use the weapon in an effective defensive manner by using the spears long shaft to pivot quickly to either side of himself to avoide an attack.
-----------------------------------------------------------------------
Expert Markmanship - Level 60
Rangers being one of the few classes adept at using a bow has learned to be truly accurate with this ranged weapon, able to target the most vital locations of an enemy, inflicting much more damage when firing a bow. 
This skill is passive and acts like Enhanced Damage except exclusively for Bow weapons. Since bows do not do very good melee damage, this skill is most effective when using the "Fire" command.
