about it more, and have possibly more information 
on which to make my argument with. The ranger is a specialized
fighter type, excelling in wilderness combat. As such,
a Ranger would possess many abilities to help them survive and fight
in such areas as a forest, or swamp, or mountains, or desert or plains.
 
Looking at the Ranger class right now, they really only have
a few area-type specific combat related abilities, being 
Quiet Movement and Camoflage for detection, Ambush for damage,
Grasping Roots for debilitation, Herbs as an accessory, and traps,
for combat assistance. 
 
As I've said before, there's only a few traps for the ranger,
and the only one thats really any use is the Pit trap.
 
Herbs, most herbs are unuseful to the mid to high level
Ranger, because they could much more easily find a potion substitute,
that is probably more powerful (because, problem with herbs,
the spell level on them is set, and is for the most part low.
this is what makes them obscelete by the time the ranger is higher
level themself. The herbs dont get any better)
 
Ambush is decent, and as always, camoflage and quiet movement are
useful.
 
If I compared this list of area-specific abilities to the lists of
specialized combat abilities Barbarians or Knights get, it would be
dwarfed. 
 
Now, i'm not proposing Rangers get the same skills, with different
names. I would like to see some more area-specific abilities for the ranger.
Over the course of the next few weeks, I will try and come up with
unique abilities that will fit the ranger profile well, by taking
advantage of the rangers surroundings, be it frozen tundra, marshy swamp,
or dry plains or desert. 
~
