Subject Ranger Skills~
Text
The Vision: I've always had a fondness in my heart for both rangers and archers in general. Therefore, I plan on throwing out several ideas and hope that maybe one of them might actually be good (some I invented myself and some I partly borrowed from other games and MUDS). Most of these ideas are focused on my vision of rangers as strategists. They rely on cunning and wit to survive against more heavily armored and strong opponents. And also after peaking at the ranger skills, I do see very large gaps in some levels (50-70, 37-45, 80+) that might need some filling.
 
Evade Traps: The more skilled ranger would be able to avoid traps rather than immediately disarming them. This allows him to disarm if he feels the need, possibly giving him a chance to recover the trap for his own use. Or it would allow him to retreat from a nearby battle and lead his victom into preplaced traps of his own.
 
Arrow Penetration: Reduces the chance of an opponent to dodge or deflect a Ranger's arrows by XX percent. (The Ranger's answer to arrow deflection, I suppose)
 
Bind Wounds: Boy scouts can do it, why not the independent and self-reliant ranger with acute knowledge of herbs and their possible healing properties?. Not to mention, if a ranger does not want to be tracked, leaving a trail of blood everywhere gets in the way.
 
Poison Arrows: The Ranger's next shot poisons the victim. Requires a bow to use. OR, we can expand on a Ranger's herbal knowledge where he can pre-poison arrows in his quiver that he can fire during the course of a battle. Poisonous effects could include ones that make the opponent sluggish and less likey to hit the enemy, a tranquilizing shot that reduces damage or nulls berserking effects, mind-numbing poisons that make it harder for casters to focus, etc.
 
Douse: Let's a Ranger quickly hide all signs of a campfire, hiding his presence in the area. (Mostly an RP tool I guess. Again inspired by the boyscouts. "Leave no trace behind!")
 
TO BE CONTINUED
~
